Uzziah: What could he be up to?
Uzziah: The Oasis Casino? The Desert Kingdom, what could he...
Izumi: Hello~Guardian.
Uzziah: ......
Izumi: Umm, though I do enjoy playing hide-and-seek so very much~ Having my every move watched over, it's really annoying.
Uzziah: ...So you've drawn me out on purpose?
Izumi: Well, I'm guessing that if I took you on myself, it would be quite a task. Might even end up hurting both of us~
Izumi: However, if it's two versus one, that won't happen.
Devious: Why do I have to clean up your mess?
Izumi: Don't be so cold-blooded, I'm here to hand over some big prey~
Uzziah: ...Tsk.
Izumi: I must return to Atlas. This "Guardian" of ours, I'll let you deal with him.
Izumi: Before the core is ready to be removed, do not let him escape~
Devious: ...Who do you think you're talking to?
Izumi: ......
Izumi: Ah yes, I'm very interested in that hidden door. Can you let me take a peek, see where it leads to?
Devious: ...It's a storage space, that is all.
Devious: What are you doing hanging around here? You had better head to the East, and continue to execute your mission!
Izumi: I have always done things according to the plan.
Izumi: As for you...isn't the progress with the Dragon Tooth worrying? Has not the True Sun been pushing you to finish the task?
Devious: Are you trying to go against your superior?
Izumi: ......
Izumi: I would never! I was just kidding~ Relax, will you? Don't be so sensitive!
Devious' Aide: High Priest, if the Great Izumi has already sensed that something is not right and sneaks into the laboratory...
Devious: This door is equipped with a special mechanism. He will not be able to enter.
Devious' Aide: Yes, sir. Should we lock this being in the lab?
Devious: No. If, in the future, he mentions anything to other members of the sect...
Devious: ...Jail is the jurisdiction of lowly humans.
Devious: We can not lock him inside.

Devious' Aide: How about locking him in the basement of the Colosseum? 

After the Queen banished the use of the Martyrs' Colosseum, there has been not even the slightest sign of life there.
Devious' Aide: The lowest level has a jail specifically designed to lock up the most dangerous criminals.
Devious: Fine, lock him up there.
Devious' Aide: Yes, sir.
Misa: High Priest, you've returned.
Devious: Holy Maiden, why haven't you rested...oh...
Misa: High Priest!
Misa: High Priest, what happened...
Misa: You're injured!?
Devious: (The Guardian...what a hassle.)
Devious: (This body is much too old. It's getting harder and harder to use...)
Devious: Holy Maiden, don't you worry about me. I merely encountered an assassin, sent by the army, that is all.
Misa: General Lazer!? They dare do such a thing!?
Devious: Do not be angry. We have no proof. Furthermore...as the Holy Maiden, you must remain calm in the face of all things.
Misa: At least...let me heal the High Priest's wounds...
Misa: ...*cough*...!...*cough*...*cough*...!
Devious: Holy Maiden!
Devious: Someone! Come now!
Devious: You must take the Holy Maiden to have her medicine!
Misa: ...*cough*...High Priest...I'm sorry...*cough*...*cough*...!
